I've been using the Laravel framework the past week.  Here's my notes to quickly set it up from scratch linux.  The application in the case is called myapp
cd ~/projects

git clone https://github.com/laravel/laravel.git</a> myapp

cd ~/projects/myapp

// storage needs to be writable by 'others' for view cache

chmod -R o+w ~/projects/myapp/storage

// create symbolic link so app can be access by http://localhost/myapp

sudo ln -s ~/projects/myapp/public /var/www/myapp


Create a database for the application

mysql -u root -p

mysql > create database myapp;


Edit configs file with your editor.  I use sublime (subl)


// use sublime to open project folder

subl ~/projects/myapp &


File: application/config/application.php

Change:

'index' => 'index.php' TO 'index' => '',

'key' => 'YourSecretKeyGoesHere!' TO 'key' => '',

'profiler' => false TO 'profiler' => true,

'timezone' => 'UTC' TO 'timezone' => 'America/Toronto',


File: application/config/application.php

Change mysql database values


Use artisan

cd ~/projects/myapp


// install migrations

php artisan migrate:install


Use table session instead of

application/config/session.php

'driver' => 'cookie' TO 'driver' => 'database',


Create table for sessions

php artisan session:table


-- Done laravel set now load bundles

